cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CC 

The paper deals with the construction and decoding properties of convolutional codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of computer search and software also suggests a possible fit in the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) due to the search for minimal field sizes.
